1
00:00:06,320 --> 00:00:07,360
They are back.

2
00:00:07,360 --> 00:00:08,680
They are back.

3
00:00:10,200 --> 00:00:11,240
I'll help you from that side.

4
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:14,600
Or you could...

5
00:00:16,840 --> 00:00:17,040
Let's go.

6
00:00:19,560 --> 00:00:20,360
Does it hurt more now?

7
00:00:20,360 --> 00:00:20,920
Yes, it really does.

8
00:00:21,360 --> 00:00:21,600
Yeah.

9
00:00:21,600 --> 00:00:22,280
It's even more swollen.

10
00:00:24,160 --> 00:00:25,720
I can't put any weight on it at all now.

11
00:00:26,080 --> 00:00:26,800
Walk slowly.

12
00:00:28,160 --> 00:00:29,080
Help!

13
00:00:29,600 --> 00:00:31,000
Take it easy, no rush.

14
00:00:31,967 --> 00:00:32,800
(Following her)

15
00:00:32,800 --> 00:00:34,400
What's he doing?

16
00:00:34,400 --> 00:00:35,240
What's this?

17
00:00:35,240 --> 00:00:37,320
Is this some kind of pain sharing?

18
00:00:37,840 --> 00:00:39,040
Why am I limping too?

19
00:00:40,400 --> 00:00:41,400
You are influenced by me.

20
00:00:41,960 --> 00:00:43,080
You are influenced by me, right?

21
00:00:43,480 --> 00:00:44,000
No,

22
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:46,240
I'm just trying to match your pace.

23
00:00:47,320 --> 00:00:47,720
See?

24
00:00:49,200 --> 00:00:50,320
Walk normally.

25
00:00:50,320 --> 00:00:53,200
No, this is more comfortable for me.

26
00:00:53,200 --> 00:00:54,200
We're both on the same rhythm.

27
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:57,400
Why are you laughing?

28
00:00:58,440 --> 00:01:00,080
They're in sync.

29
00:01:00,480 --> 00:01:01,400
So cute.

30
00:01:01,400 --> 00:01:03,320
Oh, my!

31
00:01:03,320 --> 00:01:03,800
You two.

32
00:01:03,800 --> 00:01:04,640
What's wrong?

33
00:01:05,600 --> 00:01:06,280
She's injured.

34
00:01:06,280 --> 00:01:07,120
What's going on?

35
00:01:07,120 --> 00:01:08,480
Did you sprain your ankle or what?

36
00:01:08,480 --> 00:01:09,240
It's swollen.

37
00:01:09,240 --> 00:01:10,720
Her whole leg is swollen.

38
00:01:10,720 --> 00:01:11,600
No sprain, just...

39
00:01:11,600 --> 00:01:12,200
Did she fall?

40
00:01:12,200 --> 00:01:12,840
No ankle sprain.

41
00:01:12,840 --> 00:01:13,640
That's not too bad.

42
00:01:13,640 --> 00:01:14,440
Riding that...

43
00:01:14,440 --> 00:01:15,200
At least no broken bones.

44
00:01:15,200 --> 00:01:16,280
Electric scooter.

45
00:01:16,280 --> 00:01:17,160
You fell off the scooter?

46
00:01:17,160 --> 00:01:18,360
I just...

47
00:01:18,360 --> 00:01:18,880
Fell on the ground?

48
00:01:18,880 --> 00:01:19,280
No,

49
00:01:19,280 --> 00:01:20,560
her leg directly

50
00:01:20,560 --> 00:01:22,320
fell on the step.

51
00:01:23,240 --> 00:01:24,440
Were you riding with her?

52
00:01:24,840 --> 00:01:25,720
No, we each rode one.

53
00:01:25,720 --> 00:01:26,320
He's the one who caused it.

54
00:01:26,480 --> 00:01:28,600
Zhuoran is trying to
clear his name first.

55
00:01:28,760 --> 00:01:29,600
I caused it.

56
00:01:29,600 --> 00:01:30,040
Hurry.

57
00:01:30,480 --> 00:01:31,160
Where's the knife?

58
00:01:31,160 --> 00:01:32,120
The knife?

59
00:01:32,120 --> 00:01:32,880
Bring me a knife.

60
00:01:32,880 --> 00:01:33,600
What for?

61
00:01:33,600 --> 00:01:34,640
Chop me up.

62
00:01:36,480 --> 00:01:38,000
I think you need to ice it first

63
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:39,200
and then use a warm compress tomorrow.

64
00:01:39,200 --> 00:01:40,200
She got injured yesterday

65
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:41,200
and again today.

66
00:01:41,200 --> 00:01:41,760
The wish

67
00:01:41,760 --> 00:01:44,600
of only Peixuan in this world
getting hurt...

68
00:01:44,600 --> 00:01:45,240
Not a wish.

69
00:01:45,880 --> 00:01:46,720
It's come true.

70
00:01:47,960 --> 00:01:48,400
What?

71
00:01:48,840 --> 00:01:50,160
What did you just say?

72
00:01:50,160 --> 00:01:50,720
I said,

73
00:01:50,720 --> 00:01:54,120
in this world, only Peixuan gets hurt.

74
00:01:54,600 --> 00:01:56,120
Are you even speaking human?

75
00:01:56,560 --> 00:01:57,320
Stop talking.

76
00:01:57,320 --> 00:01:57,960
Ling Lizheng.

77
00:02:01,240 --> 00:02:02,280
Easy.

78
00:02:02,680 --> 00:02:03,440
Take it slow.

79
00:02:04,160 --> 00:02:05,120
My gosh!

80
00:02:05,480 --> 00:02:06,160
How happened?

81
00:02:06,160 --> 00:02:07,440
Put your left leg down first.

82
00:02:07,440 --> 00:02:08,040
Down.

83
00:02:08,880 --> 00:02:09,880
Riding an electric scooter.

84
00:02:11,720 --> 00:02:12,680
Had a little accident.

85
00:02:14,960 --> 00:02:16,320
Are you okay?

86
00:02:16,320 --> 00:02:17,160
Have a seat first.

87
00:02:17,160 --> 00:02:18,360
Let me take a look.

88
00:02:21,680 --> 00:02:22,720
Careful.

89
00:02:23,560 --> 00:02:25,160
I'll go upstairs and get my medicine
for you,

90
00:02:25,160 --> 00:02:25,560
sweetie.

91
00:02:25,560 --> 00:02:26,160
Wait a moment.

92
00:02:26,160 --> 00:02:26,800
You have it?

93
00:02:26,800 --> 00:02:27,480
Yes,

94
00:02:28,360 --> 00:02:29,560
I have a back injury, remember?

95
00:02:29,560 --> 00:02:29,920
I'll get it for you.

96
00:02:29,920 --> 00:02:30,520
Wait a second.

97
00:02:30,520 --> 00:02:31,240
Apply it to your leg.

98
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:32,880
What happened to your foot?

99
00:02:33,320 --> 00:02:34,440
She's injured. Get some ice.

100
00:02:34,440 --> 00:02:36,120
She fell.

101
00:02:37,320 --> 00:02:38,400
How did it get so bad?

102
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:39,600
Get a plastic bag.

103
00:02:40,080 --> 00:02:42,040
(Everyone is so kind and gentle.)

104
00:02:42,040 --> 00:02:43,960
(All of them are really nice.)

105
00:02:44,360 --> 00:02:46,240
Can you walk now? No?

106
00:02:46,240 --> 00:02:47,520
I'm going to grab a stool

107
00:02:47,520 --> 00:02:49,320
and shower sitting down.

108
00:02:49,320 --> 00:02:50,120
It's fine.

109
00:02:50,120 --> 00:02:51,760
Whenever you need to
go to the bathroom tonight,

110
00:02:51,760 --> 00:02:53,000
just wake me up.

111
00:02:54,280 --> 00:02:54,680
(I'm a person)

112
00:02:54,680 --> 00:02:56,200
(who really hates to trouble others.)

113
00:02:56,200 --> 00:02:58,320
Actually, when I got back to the house,

114
00:02:58,320 --> 00:03:00,800
I was afraid everyone would

115
00:03:00,800 --> 00:03:01,880
ask what had happened to me

116
00:03:01,880 --> 00:03:02,800
and try to take care of me.

117
00:03:02,800 --> 00:03:04,160
I really hate to trouble others.

118
00:03:04,640 --> 00:03:06,040
Because she's used to being independent.

119
00:03:06,040 --> 00:03:07,240
I totally get that feeling.

120
00:03:07,240 --> 00:03:08,480
She's used to being mature.

121
00:03:08,480 --> 00:03:11,400
She's afraid of becoming a burden
to others.

122
00:03:12,760 --> 00:03:15,480
(Everyone in the house is very nice.)

123
00:03:15,480 --> 00:03:18,200
(They'll care for me and
take care of me.)

124
00:03:18,200 --> 00:03:19,840
(That makes me feel very touched.)

125
00:03:19,840 --> 00:03:20,280
Just...

126
00:03:20,280 --> 00:03:21,120
Lie down on his back first.

127
00:03:21,120 --> 00:03:22,000
Yeah, lie down first.

128
00:03:22,480 --> 00:03:24,240
The scene we wanted to see is happening.

129
00:03:24,240 --> 00:03:26,640
Finally, right?

130
00:03:26,640 --> 00:03:27,960
Alright, let's go.

131
00:03:27,960 --> 00:03:28,640
Does it hurt?

132
00:03:28,640 --> 00:03:29,920
I'll lift you a bit.

133
00:03:32,160 --> 00:03:33,680
Hold onto me tight.

134
00:03:33,680 --> 00:03:34,640
Don't be shy.

135
00:03:34,640 --> 00:03:35,880
I'm afraid I'll choke you.

136
00:03:35,880 --> 00:03:37,200
You won't.

137
00:03:37,200 --> 00:03:39,485
(Relay)

138
00:03:40,300 --> 00:03:40,400
Youling is...

139
00:03:40,920 --> 00:03:41,840
Who's lifting my butt?

140
00:03:41,840 --> 00:03:42,440
Youling, you...

141
00:03:43,280 --> 00:03:45,720
What are you trying to do to Mr. Dong?

142
00:03:45,720 --> 00:03:46,400
Wait.

143
00:03:46,400 --> 00:03:47,240
What are you doing?

144
00:03:47,920 --> 00:03:49,600
We can carry her to the balcony first.

145
00:03:49,600 --> 00:03:51,080
One, two, three, up!

146
00:03:52,560 --> 00:03:53,680
Treating me like this...

147
00:03:53,680 --> 00:03:54,320
This is nice.

148
00:03:54,320 --> 00:03:56,080
This is so sweet.

149
00:03:57,280 --> 00:03:58,040
(Full of love)
Thank you all.

150
00:03:58,560 --> 00:03:59,920
So sweet.

151
00:04:00,360 --> 00:04:00,760
Where to?

152
00:04:01,840 --> 00:04:03,240
Lean back a bit.

153
00:04:03,240 --> 00:04:04,200
(Video shot by Chen Danqi)
Don't be scared.

154
00:04:04,200 --> 00:04:05,160
Don't lean forward.

155
00:04:05,160 --> 00:04:05,720
Don't be scared.

156
00:04:05,720 --> 00:04:06,720
Lie back.

157
00:04:06,720 --> 00:04:07,200
Thank you all.

158
00:04:07,200 --> 00:04:08,040
Slow down, everyone.

159
00:04:08,040 --> 00:04:08,800
Take it easy going out.

160
00:04:08,800 --> 00:04:09,960
Watch out for the sand on the ground.

161
00:04:11,120 --> 00:04:14,400
(Years from now, this video)

162
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:15,680
(will still be a beautiful story.)

163
00:04:15,680 --> 00:04:17,240
I'm about to cry, really.

164
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:20,560
This is so cute.

165
00:04:20,920 --> 00:04:22,800
Look at the beautiful night view.

166
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:24,280
Feeling any better?

167
00:04:24,280 --> 00:04:25,560
You guys are so kind.

168
00:04:35,120 --> 00:04:37,720
Xuan and Xiaowen's

169
00:04:37,720 --> 00:04:38,760
conversation

170
00:04:38,760 --> 00:04:39,520
means a lot.

171
00:04:40,200 --> 00:04:41,320
Actually, when Xuan said

172
00:04:41,320 --> 00:04:42,480
that she doesn't know how to act cute,

173
00:04:42,480 --> 00:04:44,400
as a girl, it's a bit heartbreaking.

174
00:04:44,400 --> 00:04:46,080
You can feel she's very mature

175
00:04:46,080 --> 00:04:47,440
due to her family reasons.

176
00:04:47,440 --> 00:04:48,080
Right.

177
00:04:48,080 --> 00:04:49,240
The key is Xiaowen

178
00:04:49,240 --> 00:04:51,640
completely understood
she was acting cute.

179
00:04:51,640 --> 00:04:52,520
He fully understands

180
00:04:52,520 --> 00:04:53,760
this girl's behavior pattern.

181
00:04:53,760 --> 00:04:55,400
He interprets it very positively.

182
00:04:56,120 --> 00:04:57,440
I think he has

183
00:04:57,440 --> 00:04:58,400
more understanding

184
00:04:58,400 --> 00:04:59,920
and feelings for this girl

185
00:04:59,920 --> 00:05:01,280
than we imagined.

186
00:05:01,280 --> 00:05:02,080
He's serious.

187
00:05:02,080 --> 00:05:02,680
Yeah.

188
00:05:02,680 --> 00:05:03,680
I also want to ask everyone,

189
00:05:03,680 --> 00:05:05,960
when expressing emotions,

190
00:05:05,960 --> 00:05:08,040
are you the type to say it directly,

191
00:05:08,040 --> 00:05:09,400
like saying "I love you", "I like you",

192
00:05:09,400 --> 00:05:09,840
"I miss you"

193
00:05:09,840 --> 00:05:11,600
frequently?

194
00:05:11,600 --> 00:05:12,200
Or are you the type

195
00:05:12,200 --> 00:05:13,240
who compresses love

196
00:05:13,240 --> 00:05:14,720
into actions

197
00:05:14,720 --> 00:05:16,200
to let the other feel it?

198
00:05:16,680 --> 00:05:18,760
Since I was a kid, my parents and I

199
00:05:18,760 --> 00:05:21,000
have never been good
at directly expressing

200
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:22,640
emotions like "I love you"
or "I miss you".

201
00:05:23,480 --> 00:05:24,640
Once, by chance,

202
00:05:24,640 --> 00:05:25,400
I was chatting with my dad,

203
00:05:25,400 --> 00:05:26,400
and I realized that

204
00:05:26,880 --> 00:05:28,880
these emotions aren't as that heavy
as I thought.

205
00:05:28,880 --> 00:05:29,360
Right.

206
00:05:29,840 --> 00:05:31,080
Sometimes my parents

207
00:05:31,080 --> 00:05:33,160
might say they don't need it,

208
00:05:33,160 --> 00:05:33,760
but actually,

209
00:05:33,760 --> 00:05:36,120
they're just used to expressing
that way.

210
00:05:36,120 --> 00:05:36,720
There was this one time,

211
00:05:36,720 --> 00:05:39,520
I made him a really expensive meal,

212
00:05:39,520 --> 00:05:40,120
you know,

213
00:05:40,120 --> 00:05:41,240
and he said, "Don't."

214
00:05:41,240 --> 00:05:42,560
Then the next second,
he'd be like, "Look,

215
00:05:42,560 --> 00:05:43,120
This is what my son

216
00:05:43,120 --> 00:05:44,160
made for me today."

217
00:05:44,600 --> 00:05:45,600
He immediately posted it on Moments.

218
00:05:45,680 --> 00:05:47,400
Right.

219
00:05:47,400 --> 00:05:48,080
So I realized

220
00:05:48,080 --> 00:05:49,320
they actually still need it.

221
00:05:50,280 --> 00:05:52,000
Actually, in Chinese tradition,

222
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:54,520
it's about being quick in action
and slow in speech.

223
00:05:55,480 --> 00:05:58,800
We might think that expressing love

224
00:05:58,800 --> 00:06:00,920
and showing care through actions

225
00:06:00,920 --> 00:06:01,800
is enough.

226
00:06:01,800 --> 00:06:02,400
Yes.

227
00:06:02,400 --> 00:06:04,320
If you express it in words,

228
00:06:04,320 --> 00:06:05,160
it becomes lighter,

229
00:06:05,160 --> 00:06:07,480
and it might even diminish the love.

230
00:06:08,320 --> 00:06:09,640
Personally, I've always thought

231
00:06:09,640 --> 00:06:11,240
that I'm someone who is good at saying

232
00:06:11,240 --> 00:06:12,360
(Shen Yifei)
"I love you".

233
00:06:12,360 --> 00:06:12,800
Because I believe

234
00:06:12,800 --> 00:06:14,120
this can be practiced deliberately.

235
00:06:14,120 --> 00:06:14,600
Right.

236
00:06:14,600 --> 00:06:15,680
So in today's culture,

237
00:06:15,680 --> 00:06:17,040
maybe actions and words

238
00:06:17,040 --> 00:06:19,320
need to match.

239
00:06:19,320 --> 00:06:20,560
That's a better way

240
00:06:20,560 --> 00:06:23,120
to make others feel loved.

241
00:06:23,120 --> 00:06:23,760
Yes.

242
00:06:29,880 --> 00:06:31,040
Isn't that Liu?

243
00:06:31,040 --> 00:06:32,360
Yeah, she looks really unhappy

244
00:06:32,360 --> 00:06:33,680
and melancholic.

245
00:06:34,040 --> 00:06:34,720
What's wrong?

246
00:06:34,720 --> 00:06:35,880
You look unhappy.

247
00:06:42,560 --> 00:06:43,560
She just went upstairs.

248
00:06:43,560 --> 00:06:45,200
Perhaps, she doesn't want to face him.

249
00:07:03,960 --> 00:07:04,960
Did you eat the watermelon?

250
00:07:04,960 --> 00:07:06,040
Wasn't the watermelon taken upstairs?

251
00:07:07,120 --> 00:07:07,880
Okay.

252
00:07:08,440 --> 00:07:08,840
Okay?

253
00:07:10,360 --> 00:07:11,240
What does "okay" mean?

254
00:07:11,240 --> 00:07:12,400
Youling, what's on your mind?

255
00:07:13,720 --> 00:07:14,640
Looks like everyone

256
00:07:14,640 --> 00:07:16,040
has gone through
some small troubles today.

257
00:07:16,040 --> 00:07:17,120
We shouldn't be here

258
00:07:18,080 --> 00:07:18,720
acting mischievously.

259
00:07:18,720 --> 00:07:19,160
Mischievously.

260
00:07:19,160 --> 00:07:20,120
Then let's go out.

261
00:07:20,120 --> 00:07:21,480
Go to study then.

262
00:07:21,480 --> 00:07:22,040
Go to work.

263
00:07:23,200 --> 00:07:23,880
It's mainly...

264
00:07:25,720 --> 00:07:26,640
No, I can tell you.

265
00:07:28,040 --> 00:07:29,480
Wait, right here, no need to go too far.

266
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:31,600
Youling still wants to talk to someone.

267
00:07:33,040 --> 00:07:35,400
I originally thought

268
00:07:35,400 --> 00:07:36,600
her being like this all day

269
00:07:36,600 --> 00:07:38,000
might have something to do with me.

270
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:39,720
Maybe because

271
00:07:39,720 --> 00:07:41,760
what I said to her yesterday
was too harsh.

272
00:07:42,480 --> 00:07:43,800
- What you said yesterday?
- Right.

273
00:07:44,520 --> 00:07:46,000
Don't you think

274
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:47,600
she's just sulking?

275
00:07:48,840 --> 00:07:49,080
No,

276
00:07:49,880 --> 00:07:51,880
what's the point of sulking?

277
00:07:53,240 --> 00:07:54,840
Youling has a soft heart after all.

278
00:07:55,320 --> 00:07:56,240
He feels a bit sorry for her.

279
00:07:56,920 --> 00:07:58,360
Was what you said yesterday

280
00:07:58,360 --> 00:08:00,000
pretty much

281
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:01,120
the same as what you told me later

282
00:08:01,120 --> 00:08:02,680
when there were other girls around?

283
00:08:02,680 --> 00:08:04,160
Or was it harsher?

284
00:08:04,160 --> 00:08:04,760
Not harsher.

285
00:08:04,760 --> 00:08:06,080
I just said, "What do you mean now?"

286
00:08:06,080 --> 00:08:07,400
Then she said she was confused,

287
00:08:07,400 --> 00:08:09,840
and she hadn't figured it out.

288
00:08:09,840 --> 00:08:10,200
Confused.

289
00:08:10,200 --> 00:08:11,800
I said, "Forget it then."

290
00:08:11,800 --> 00:08:12,600
And I left.

291
00:08:12,600 --> 00:08:13,360
I stood up and walked away.

292
00:08:13,360 --> 00:08:14,720
Then she called me,

293
00:08:14,720 --> 00:08:16,000
and I said,
